@BGRNDSTART{{}}

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{kotonisuru}}}} indicates a volitional decision, it's focus is on who is going to take the action.
In this respect it differs from <a href="grammar-koto-ni-naru.html">@HI{{kotoninaru}}</a>, which indicates a non-volitional decision.
@HI{{@EM{{kotonisuru}}}} is a more complex form of <a href="grammar-ni-suru.html">@N{{}}@HI{{nisuru}}</a>, where the noun is replaced with a nominalised phrase.

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{capital^metropolis}}made@KT{{basu}}de@KJ{{going}}ku<strong>kotonishimashou</strong.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Let's go as far as Kyoto by bus.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{every^day^Sino-^character}}wo@KJ{{ten}}@KJ{{memorize}}eru<strong>kotonishimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I've decided to memorise ten kanji every day.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
To say that one has decided not to do something, negate the verb before @HI{{@EM{{kotonisuru}}}}.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{pikunikku}}ni@KJ{{going}}kouto@KJ{{think}}ttandesuga,@KJ{{going}}kanai@EM{{kotonishimashita}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I thought I would go to the picnic, but I decided not to.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
The form @HI{{@EM{{kotonishiteiru}}}} indicates that the decision is still in force.
This is a previously decided habit.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{every^weekday^weekday^day}}no@KJ{{night}}ha@KJ{{outside}}de@KJ{{eat^matter}}wosuru@EM{{kotonishiteiru}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      We make it a rule to eat out on Sunday evening.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
The form @HI{{@EM{{kotonishiteiru}}}} with a negative form indicates that a previous decision
not to do something is still in force.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{meat}}woamari@KJ{{eat}}benai<strong>kotonishiteiru</strong.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I make it a rule not to eat very much meat.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

